members.title: Standard Sequence
members.text: Given the strata are undisturbed, the Primary strata are overlain by Cambrian strata, Silurian strata, Old Red Sandstone strata, Mountain Limestone strata, Coal Measures strata, New Red Sandstone strata and Oolitic stata, respectively #pri

members.title: Standard Sequence
members.argumentTitle: Standard Sequence as Partition - Main Culm

members.title: Formation of strata
members.text: Strata are originally formed from sediments that were deposited in flat horizontal sheets - the younger sediments deposited on older ones. #pri

members.title: Unbroken Sequence of Devon Strata
members.text: In Devon, all the strata - older than the New Red Sandstone - form an unbroken sequence of strata #ev

members.title: CM Plants in Devon Culm
members.text: Near Bideford (North Devon), there are CM fossil plants in the main part of the Culm strata (in close association with seams of imperfect anthracite) #ev

members.title: North of Exmoor
members.text: Passing Exmoor northwards, the strata become older #ev

members.title: Trough through Exmoor
members.text: There is a trough through Exmoor - formed by a band of limestone running out to the north coast at Ilfracombe and south of Barnstaple #ev

members.title: Characteristic Rock Types
members.text: A rock type r is characteristic for some time interval dt iff (i) r only exisits during dt and (ii) during dt, every region supports r #dat-met

members.title: Existence of Characteristic Rock Types
members.text: For every time intervall dt, there is some charactersitic rock type r #dat-met

members.title: CRTP - 2
members.text: If two strata support the same characteristic rock types, then they are of the same age #dat-met

members.title: Characteristic Rock Type Principle
members.text: There is a bijection between the age of some strata t and its characteristic rock types #dat-met
